✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Good idea. Not easy, not hard.
Don't you think it'd be more fun if make a case with negative numbers ? Or it is too difficult to program ?

Goal
* Please format "res" and "n" as [[variables]].

* Please fix the typo: "lexicographicaly" => "lexicographically".

Input
* Line 1: Description does not seem to be complete.

* Line 2: Please change "description" to "combination".

Output
* Please format all variables.

* The meaning of "lexicographic order" may be moved to Goal section and please format all the x and y variables.

* Please mention "one combination per line".

Thanks.

Note:
There's another clash on partitioning an integer:
https://www.codingame.com/contribute/view/694936cd472186ff4bf7d243d16738464846
but that clash requires output of
• combinations of positive (instead of non-negative) integers,
• all lengths (instead of specified length), and
• reverse lexicographical order (instead of lexicographical order).

I guess this clash is sufficiently different from the approved one.
What exactly do you mean? Do you mean to program an edge case? Do you want to also take in a lower bar and use it with it?
You could ! It's still a great idea to test a new edge case
